SECTION 1: THE QCD TRACE ANOMALY
================================================================================

THE TRACE ANOMALY
=================

In classical QCD, the stress-energy tensor is traceless for massless quarks:

    T^μ_μ = 0   (classical)

Quantum effects break this symmetry. The trace anomaly is:

    ⟨T^μ_μ⟩ = (β(g)/2g) × ⟨G^a_μν G^{a,μν}⟩ + Σ_q m_q ⟨q̄q⟩

where:
    - β(g) = -b₀g³/(16π²) + ... is the QCD beta function
    - b₀ = 11 - 2N_f/3 = 11 - 2(6)/3 = 7 for 6 flavors
    - G^a_μν is the gluon field strength
    - m_q ⟨q̄q⟩ are the quark condensate contributions

THE PROTON MASS DECOMPOSITION
=============================

The proton mass can be decomposed as (Ji, 1995):

    M_p = ⟨p| T^μ_μ |p⟩ = M_gluon + M_quark + M_trace + M_QED

where:
    M_gluon:  Gluon kinetic energy and self-interactions
    M_quark:  Quark kinetic energy
    M_trace:  Trace anomaly contribution
    M_QED:    Electromagnetic corrections (small)


--- Ji's Lattice QCD Results ---

Proton mass decomposition (Ji, 1995; Yang et al., 2018):
--------------------------------------------------
  Quark energy        : 1/3 = 33.3%
  Gluon energy        : 1/3 = 33.3%
  Trace anomaly       : 1/4 = 25.0%
  Quark mass          : 1/12 = 8.3%
--------------------------------------------------
  Total               : 1 = 100.0%

  Gluon field total (energy + anomaly): 7/12 = 58.3%

  Note: 1/3 + 1/4 = 7/12 ≈ 0.583
        But pure glue (no anomaly mixing) ≈ 2/5 = 0.400

